latestIgtvVideos.title: REPAINT BED UNDER ₹500 using common Indian products! ✨
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
I always found my sofa-bed to be perfect for my room because of the vintage grill, durable sheesham wood and it’s size. However, the surface had tarnished and it had become boring. Here’s how I revamped my room especially my bed into more of a minimal aesthetic. 
My sister( @anika._.art ) helped me paint it and we painted it in under ₹500!!! Here’s what we used : * Sandpaper 3pc x ₹15 = ₹45
* Brushes 2pc x ₹30 = ₹60
* Berger wood white primer 1pc 500ml = ₹90
* Berger Luxol hi-gloss white colour enamel 1pc 500ml = ₹150
* Paint Thinner 1 bottle = ₹50
* We had acrylic paint already but the small tube i.e 40 ml costs about = ₹100

Grand total = ₹495 🤩 .

latestIgtvVideos.title: Update! Gel nail paint removal at home and giving my nails a break! 🌿
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
The intro screen recordings are to show when these videos were made. That is 22.october and 23.novemever. 💖

A month ago I made a video on how I paint my nails at home which last a month. This video is an update to my previous IGTV.
I don’t like my nails too long and I have my exams coming up (not comfy to write with long nails) so it was the time to cut them and give them a break. 
I used my electric nail drill machine with a corn like ceramic nail drill bit to remove the paint, I buffed them (yellow buffer) to smoothen the surface, cut them, filed them to give them a rounded square shape. 
To keep them strong I used to a strengthening solution by Onails and moisturised by hands with OPI hand cream. 
And yes, I used a breathing mask all through the procedure because I don’t like breathing in the resin powder of the paint. 
Also, this procedure is totally painless unless you carelessly put too much pressure on the nail with the ceramic drill. 
Overall, I haven’t seen any harm of this procedure on my nails.. Let me know what you think 🌻 .
.

I got these different sized rollers from Amazon India and since then whenever I get time, I try to style my hair like this! 
Even though the perfect results would stay just for a day but the bounce and volume remains until the next hair wash. ✨

Things I used here:
1. Tangle teezer to brush out my wet hair gently
2. Tresemme gloss ultimate heat protectant (love this one)
